alwaysApply: true
rules:
  # Code Quality Overview
  - Cursor should run lint, prettier, format after each series of changes
  - Verify JavaScript/Vue.js code before building: `npm run build`
  - All code must pass ESLint, Prettier, and Vue.js checks before commit
  - Use Conventional Commits for all commit messages:
    - Commit messages must follow format: `type(scope): description`
  
  # Linting and Formatting Standards
  - All code must pass ESLint checks before commit
  - All code must pass Prettier formatting checks before commit
  - All code must pass Vue.js linting checks before commit
  - Use `npm run lintfix` to automatically fix ESLint issues
  - Use `npm run lint` to check for linting errors
  - Use `npm run build` to verify build process
  
  # Naming Conventions
  - **Files**: Use kebab-case (`user-profile.vue`, `access-log.vue`)
  - **Components**: Use PascalCase (`UserProfile`, `AccessLog`)
  - **Mixins**: Use camelCase with descriptive names (`userProfileMixin`, `accessLogMixin`)
  - **Store Modules**: Use camelCase (`userModule`, `accessLogModule`)
  - **Constants**: Use SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (`API_ENDPOINTS`, `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`)
  - **Functions**: Use camelCase with descriptive names (`getUserProfile`, `validateAccessLog`)
  
  # JavaScript/Vue.js Standards
  - Use ES6+ features (arrow functions, destructuring, template literals)
  - Use proper Vue.js component structure (template, script, style)
  - Use proper Vue.js lifecycle hooks and methods
  - Use proper Vue.js data, computed, and watch patterns
  - Use proper Vue.js props and events
  - Define proper return types for all functions
  
  # Code Organization
  - Keep component files under 200 lines; split into smaller components if larger
  - Use index.js files for clean imports from folders with multiple exports
  - Co-locate test files with their corresponding source files
  - Group related files in feature-based folders when they exceed 5 files
  - Use proper Vue.js component structure and organization
  
  # Cross-References
  - Shell command permissions: `01-core/05-shell-command-permissions.mdc`
  - Vue patterns: `02-technical/01-vue-patterns.mdc`
  - Project structure: `02-technical/04-project-structure.mdc`
  - Testing standards: `02-technical/09-testing-standards.mdc`
